Darren Evans-Young <darren(-at-)bama.ua.edu> wrote:  On Mon, 22 May 2006, Kevin H. Roberts wrote:

>As far as overheating, the finger on the dipstick test is great.  The
>main thing that I found was sealing the engine compartment.

In my case, I had replaced my original heater fan with 2 bilge blowers.
Well, I didnt think about the fact that they didnt have flaps, so my
engine fan was sucking in hot air from the heat exchangers. Once I
realized what was going on and plugged the hole until I could figure
out a solution, my head and oil temps dropped about 30 degrees F.

